Business Brief -- Bell Atlantic Corp.:
   Cellular Unit to Streamline
   Phone Access to Its Services
Bell Atlantic, based in Philadelphia, said it plans to
acquire rights to the new software-based technology, and
would introduce it first in the Baltimore-Washington market
this summer. The company plans to price the service at $15 or
$25 a month, depending on various features a customer
selects.
   Last month, Bell Atlantic announced it was testing a
Motorola Inc. system in Pittsburgh that would also provide
customers with a single phone number for various types of
phone service.